creating a text file with command line interface
.>>>echo "text content" > fileName.ext
---using ren command to rename files
.>>>ren targetFileName newFileName
---copying files:
.>>>copy newDoc.docx backUp.docx --creates a copy of newDoc and saves it as backUp
##You can also specify the destiation
.>>>copy newDoc.docx DeatinationMap(C:\Users\GODSWILL\cardealership-app\newDoc)
---moving a document:
.>>>move fileName DeatinationMap(C:\Users\GODSWILL\cardealership-app)

========
    *GIT COMMANDS*
FOR GIT CONFIGURATION
in your windows powershell
.>>>git config --global user.name "Goddy-2024"
.>>>git config --global user.email "gaoajuoga@gmail.com"
.>>>git init (initializes git in a project)
.>>>git add . (adds all the files in the environment directory to the reinitialized git repo C:/Users/GODSWILL/cardealership-app/.git/)
.>>>git commit -m "Adds a commit message"
.>>>git remote add origin https://github.com/Goddy-2024/PowerlearnProject/DAY1 -- connects remotely and adds the reinitialised virtual repo to the remote repository according to the url
.>>>git push origin master -- pushes the changes to the remote repo

=====
***DOWNLOADING A PROJECT FROM GITHUB***
.>>>git config --global user.name "Goddy-2024"
.>>>git config --global user.email "gaoajuoga@gmail.com"
.>>>git init (initializes git in a project)
.>>>git clone https://github.com/Goddy-2024/PowerlearnProject.git
THE FILES ARE SAVED IN THE WORKING DIRECTORY


